name: Brownie Cheesecake Cupcakes
author: Kat
summary: Kind of like cheesecake-swirled brownies but made in cupcake cups. Easy to make with package brownie mix. Also cheesecake mix doesn't contain eggs.
ingredients: 1 (18.25 ounce) package brownie mix (such as Pillsbury®)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners
Mix brownie mix, oil, eggs, and water together in a bowl until well combined
Mix cream cheese, sugar, butter, flour, and vanilla extract together in a separate bowl
Fill each muffin cup 1/2-full with brownie mix; top with cream cheese mixture
Spoon brownie mix over cream cheese mixture layer
Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted in the center of the brownie part comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes
